Ppl w ADHD deserve understanding, especially in medical communities. A neurotypical person doesn’t understand what it’s like to navigate as an ADHD sufferer & Vice versa. We deserve effective treatment. We deserve to not be expected to just live the way neurotypicals do.

Awareness for ppl w ADHD is more important now than ever. I’ve tried medications that didn’t do anything but take my personality away & leave me numb, & I’ve tried medications (like Adderrall) that didn’t do anything at all. More effective treatments NEED to be found.

ADHD has a plethora of symptoms that make it nearly impossible to live a productive life without some form of help. I often feel like I don’t fit in. Like there’s no place for me in the world. Like I’m burdening everybody.

Many ppl w ADHD cannot explain why they couldn’t do something. ADHD IS BRAIN DAMAGE. Someone w ADHD may not b able to explain it, but executive dysfunction is caused by damage to these areas of the brain. Vital areas. https://t.co/3yoDAIiHAJ

ADHD is brain damage, literally. This is called executive dysfunction. The parts of ur brain that allow u to manage the most vital functions are severely damaged & WILL NOT function without treatment. This is the reason why many productivity methods do not work on ADHD. https://t.co/iwyIykZrvi https://t.co/X78LHoYrun

I have an extremely selective & short term memory. Many ppl have tried to use tips & tricks to help me like making lists of tasks, but I don’t respond to that. It doesn’t work on me. I just ignore the list or become overwhelmed by it & shut down completely & do nothing instead.

I liken ADHD to the sunken place from Get Out. It feels like I’m a passenger in my body when I’m trying to complete tasks, like cleaning or reading or just reaching for something right next to me. I’m in my head screaming & begging to just do it, but my body will not move. https://t.co/YrauZTsm6a

I struggle w ADHD, agoraphobia, depression, & CPTSD. It’s very difficult for me to live a “normal” life, but even w all this, ADHD is the only disorder I wish I could magically be free from. It has absolutely ruined aspects of my life.

More ppl need to understand what a prison severe ADHD is. A lot of ppl think it’s being unable to pay attention or being hyperactive. ADHD is the absolute most difficult aspect of my life & I desperately would love to b effectively treated for it. It is hellish at times.

I’ll do everything in my power to to make everyone laugh, think, & love themselves more. Soon I will get back to helping create crowdfunds. I love helping others, & I will continue to again. I will get back to the things I love. I will give back what I’ve been given, ten fold.

All I can really give to this earth is my authentic self. I used to think that wasn’t enough but the messages I’ve gotten today have proven to me that it it’s more than enough. Thank you everyone, especially @TheConfidentHoe. You uplifted me more than you realize today!

No matter how many times I have fallen, made mistakes, didn’t do what was best, there have been “strangers” rushing to my side to pick me back up. That is rare, & I am eternally grateful. I wish I had a way to thank all of you in a way that felt more meaningful. Some day I will.

I often can’t see what I’ve done to deserve the amount of support I receive. I don’t give myself credit. My inbox is filled w kindness, love, support, & acceptance from ppl I considered strangers. I never thought I deserved this, but now I am accepting that maybe I do!

To hear that I’ve uplifted someone on their worst days, given them a smile when they thought they couldn’t smile again, being told I’ve helped someone find their voice. Find their confidence. There is nothing in the world that can measure up to how good that feels. I am honored.

Want to go back to being able to help others instead of being the one that needs help. I’m overwhelmed & humbled by how much others want to help me. I don’t acknowledge how much I’ve given some of you, so I appreciate the reminder that I’ve made positive impacts. Thank you all.

squid game was a fun watch. It wasn’t complicated or ground breaking. The plot was very spoon-fed & easy to understand. I don’t see how anybody couldn’t see it for what it was. I’ll definitely watch the next season bc I enjoy the talent, but come on y’all. Not rocket science. Lol

And it’s how the world is. Low class ppl fight tooth & nail for a fraction of what the rich have, & we turn against each other before we even think to turn against the rich, who use us like puppets. Squid game is not high fantasy, it’s extremely real.

A lot of us are two bad weeks away from playing in squid game. If it were real, a lot of us would be there, willingly playing that game like the ppl in the show. That’s a part of the point. And a lot of rich folks would be right there betting on us, watching us die.

It’s not about what “scumbags will do for money.” It’s about what REGULAR PEOPLE would do for money & the way rich people view the lower class: meaningless insects playing a game. You’re meant to ask yourself what YOU would do if you had no other options.

While it is allegorical, the allegory isn’t hard to navigate. It’s spoon fed. Squid game wanted to accomplish their criticism of capitalism, & they did. Very easily & pretty well. So how the fuck do so many people not understand. Is it just American audiences that don’t “get it”?

Even as an English speaker, squid game was ridiculously easy to understand. It was pretty much spoon-fed to us. There wasn’t as much ~deep symbolism~ as ppl seem to think. I’m not saying the show was bad, I’m saying the show was extremely simple. VERY simple.

But even for a non-Korean speaker, I understood the characters & point of the plot just fine. When I watched a Korean speaker break down parts in Korean that I wouldn’t understand, it didn’t change my understanding of the show. It remained the same. Nothing changed.

& a lot of ppl blamed poor translation. As an American who doesn’t speak korean, I understand there are a lot of Korean phrases that don’t translate to English well & were instead replaced w something else. I understand that I missed certain details that Koreans understand.

I enjoyed watching it. Prolly won’t watch it again. Prolly won’t even remember it really. It was good, & it did serve its purpose in critiquing capitalism & the lack of humanity in class division, but to see this many ppl unable to figure out the message is aggravating lol

The point of squid game is so obvious & IN UR FACE that I don’t understand how this many ppl can’t comprehend it. It’s not as high fantasy as ppl think—rich ppl LITERALLY comfortably sit & watch poor ppl LITERALLY kill themselves & each other to survive in capitalist societies
